      "text": [
        ": مَنْ قَالَ فِی کُلِّ یَوْمٍ سَبْعَ مَرَّاتٍ الْحَمْدُ لِلَّهِ عَلَی کُلِّ نِعْمَهٍ کَانَتْ أَوْ هِیَ کَائِنَهٌ فَقَدْ أَدَّی شُکْرَ مَا مَضَی وَ شُکْرَ مَا بَقِیَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
          "1. It was narrated to me by Muhammad b. al-Hassan al-Saffar from Ya’qub b. Yazid from Muhammad b. Abi ’Umayr from Muhammad b. Uthman from Burayd from his brother al-Hussain from Umar b. Bazee’ from the one who mentioned it from Abi Abdillah (a.s.) who said: “One who recites: Al- h’amdulillaahi a’laa kulli ni’matin kaanat wa hiyaa kaa-inah seven times a day, has thanked (Allah) for the past and he has thanked (Allah) for the future.”"
        ]
      }
